Some people are really great at asking for things, they have no problem whatsoever! 

Some people find it REALLY CHALLENGING to ask. 

2 main reasons it can be hard to ask is: 

1) being scared of rejection or a no, probbably because when you asked for things when you were young and received a no in some way, it may have been really painful. It could have felt like rejection so that NO can bring up a deeper idea of self which is that you don’t deserve or it means something about you as a person. 

2) You don’t want to put the other person out or imposition them. In other words, you may feel overly responsible for someone else’s experience and therefore it’s just easier not to ask. 

Do either of these resonate with you if you have trouble asking for things?

Share an emoji in the comments below on what emotion is coming up for you right now 👇🏼

Stop 🛑 judging emotions as good or bad, wrong or right. 

An emotion is something that swells 🌀 up inside of you. 

Too many people confuse emotions as feelings. And because of the therapy, “I FEEL” phrase (which is really helpful to get more in touch with one’s own feelings) people hang thoughts and opinions as feelings. 

I feel that you did this because....
or 
I feel that the color of that is...

Those are opinions, senses, observations, etc....but those are not emotions. 

Anger, frustration, hurt, grief, sadness, happiness—those are emotions. 

They come up ⬆️ they go down ⬇️

They turn left ⬅️ they turn right ➡️

They may come up again, and go away. They are there to surface and for you to use them to guide you to expressing and releasing and bringing in. 

If you keep judging them and labelling them, you may likely repress them and then they get stuck. 

Stuck emotions cause problems. Physical, health, mental and emotional. 

Have you caught yourself judging your emotions lately?

#emotions #emotional #selflove #love #expressyourself #expression #randyspellingcoaching #lifecoach #coaching

3 quick hacks on how to elevate your mood:
 
🏃MOVEMENT: Move your body, it doesn’t matter how you do this, just get your heart pumping and blood flowing through your body. This could be as simple as a power walk around your neighborhood, lifting some weights for 10 minutes, doing some laps in a pool, playing a quick game of tennis or football with your kids -YOU DECIDE. Try this for 10 minutes and watch your mood elevate.
 
☀️SUNLIGHT: Let the sun hit your skin. I like to look at it like a solar panel, the more skin you can expose to the sun the more you will charge up your body. You only need to do this for 10 minutes to feel the benefits. *Please ensure you are being sun smart (use protection where needed) and be mindful how long you expose yourself to the direct sunlight. You know your body best so follow what feels right.
 
🧘🏻‍♀️SELF CARE: Self-care is so commonly overlooked, yet the positive impacts on your overall mood when you do something to care for self is powerful.   What is it that fills up your cup? What can you do or experience that you know always makes you feel good?   This is where you need to look within as we will have different needs depending on what we are feeling in that given moment. Tune in, do you need some ‘me time’ to take a bath, booking yourself in for a massage or simply reading a few chapters of your book, play a game with your children or phone a friend for a nourishing conversation - however this looks for you, take that first step and care for SELF! This goes a long way.   Share what tools you use to elevate your mood?

How I stepped off the ‘busy’ treadmill and started to live more peacefully.

And it didn’t include yoga and meditation. 

Living your life with this never ending to-do list with family commitments, work demands, social events, household tasks (and the list goes on), can feel overwhelming and stressful, not to mention draining on your energy. 

Being in this GO GO state often, can cause your brain to automatically function in this state, to the point that when you STOP you feel fidgety, as if there is still more to do.

You can reverse this by simply paying attention to when you feel this wave taking over, take a step back and slow it down. 

Intentionally set aside time for nothing to do but relax, restore and just be - give yourself this permission. 

By practicing peace you will automatically become more peaceful. 
 
Can you relate to this busy state of being? If so let me know in the comments below 👇🏼 

#busy #busybusy #beintentional #lifecoaching #lifecoachingtips #tip #randyspellingcoaching #mindset #designyourlife #lifebydesign

I’m fascinated by the construct of time ⏰

The body, doesn’t really know time because the moment the mind thinks it’s a certain time, the body responds. 

When you vividly remember a very stressful, painful or traumatic time in life, the body starts responding as if it were back there. 

Same goes for good memories as well! We are locked into this grid of time, this construct of a 24 hour a day period and then, 2 days a year (until this officially changes) we just gain or lose an hour and that’s just that. 

You may react to this gain or loss, but what if it were 2 hours, 3 hours, etc...it seems like time can be rather fungible and we adapt to it accordingly. 

Really just makes me wonder, if we accepted that we are in the consctruct of time, what happens if we accept that we can go out of the construct of time, what happens then?

I would love to know your thoughts!
#time #timemanagement #daylightsavings #lifecoachingtips #lifecoach #mindsetcoach #whatistime #growthmindset

Fathers - You are more powerful than you know. 
You have the power to co-create, the power to destroy.
The power to uplift, the power to bring joy.

The power to make a difference, to be a shining light.

I’m sitting here looking at my half-dead Bonsai tree 🌳

I got it as a gift, and I was so excited about it. 

If you know anything about Bonsais, you know they are notorious for being quite finicky. (Spoiler alert: they are finicky. lol)

Things were going well. I was making sure it was getting plenty of light, water, & food.  Then, I had a trip. 

I'd planned to be away for a few days, but life had other plans & that trip stretched to about a week & a half. Which meant my little plant didn’t get any water while I was gone. 

So I came home to a half-dead Bonsai. 

Over the past several weeks, I’ve really had to get to know what this plant needs and it’s been an interesting journey.

Because something happened as I spent time with this plant. 

Maybe it's the empath in me, but I began identifying with it. 

Feeling its rhythms, sensing its needs. 

I moved it around the room, helping it find the perfect light 🌞 to thrive. 

I even started placing a couple of ice cubes for that slow, nourishing watering technique and it got me thinking 🤔

It's such a profound gift, to care for something - be it a plant or even as a parent. 

We sometimes overlook these daily nuances of care. 

With my Bonsai, it wasn't about placing it where I thought it looked best, but understanding its unique needs & its own wisdom then making shifts according to that. 

I had to find where it would grow best. 

My Bonsai plant still has a ways to go, but it’s hanging in there.

Maybe you’re in a similar boat? Just hanging in there. Clinging to the leaves you have left.

Like my Bonsai, we all need to find where we'll grow the best. 

It's all about nurturing, understanding, & truly listening to what our inner selves demand. 

Maybe you’ve been feeling stagnant. Or maybe even worse than stagnant. Like you’re regressing.

And like my Bonsai, maybe you’re not getting what you need to grow. 

But with the right care, the right environment, & the right understanding, growth becomes inevitable.

If you ever feel like that struggling Bonsai, maybe it's time to discover the nurturing you truly need.

What nurturing do you feel that you need right now?

#nurture #selfcare #growthjourney #selflove
